		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<i><b>AND I'm not implying that in the&nbsp;hardest hitting raid encounters<br><br></b></i>It didn't say raid encounters Darknyss. Hijacking Warrior uniqueness by confining it to raid encounters is way beyond expecting shield appropriate weapons and an end to the Knight monopoly.<br><i><b><br>your physical mitigation abilities are unmatched<br></b></i><br>It didn't say mitigation Darknyss, it said unmatched <u>survival</u>. Hijacking Warrior uniqueness by pretending raw mitigation can be fairly exceeded by mitigation and combat self-heals when it said unmatched survival, not unmatched mitigation is way beyond
expecting shield appropriate weapons and an end to the Knight monopoly. <br><br><b><i>SURVIVING is not Warrior unique.</i></b><br><br>Unmatched surviving is Warrior unique Darknyss. That's what unmatched means - unique, without peer, ....<br><br>Hijacking Warrior uniqueness by pretending "unmatched" means "matched" is way beyond
expecting shield appropriate weapons and an end to the Knight monopoly.<br><br><i><b>Snare, Stuns, Roots... those are unique...</b></i><br>Shields, non-single class SWORDS, .... those are not unique Darknyss. Two of the three classes that commonly tank share such swords attesting to the fact that they are not unique.<br><br>It is pretty funny that you really can in one breath suggest destroying the only reason to play a Warrior (go ahead, poll Warirors and see how many expected to be the tank that suceeded vs. some cutting edge mobs hybrids died to) as if that wasn't eliminating our central uniqueness....<br><br>And in the next act like swords are SK or Paladin class unique or that Paladins and SK's are a single class.<div></div>	
