			<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR><BR>Unmatched surviving is Warrior unique Darknyss. That's what unmatched means - unique, without peer, ....<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>No it's not... it's impossible... there's a million and one ways in which every class has the ability to survive where a Warrior doesn't.&nbsp; An Enchanter can mezz a mob indefinitely and never get hit, a Cleric can heal all the damage done to them... an FD class can survive by dropping all aggro.</P>
<P>Your unmatched survival pertains to nothing more than having unrivaled pure physical mitigation (although you could probably make a good&nbsp;argument for spellbased mitigation as well).</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:</P>
<P>Shields, non-single class SWORDS, .... those are not unique Darknyss. Two of the three classes that commonly tank share such swords attesting to the fact that they are not unique.
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Knight melee is exactly the same in every single respect, aside from situational slays.&nbsp; They were made with Knights in mind.&nbsp; They have every reason to be Knight specific just as weapons with only WAR/ROG/BRD/RNG do NOT include Knights.</P>
<P>You don't get Monk/Bst 1hander and 2hand blunts.... They're not a single class... but they're not designed for you.</P>
<P>Get over it... you can't have everything.</P>
