		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Sometimes BB gets portrayed as being inconsistent unfairly.&nbsp; I think this is one of those times.</P>
<P>He seems quite consistent to me in this...</P>
<P>The description says "Unmatched ability to survive the most brutal battles".&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>This implies being engaged in battle while this "ability" is being expressed.&nbsp;&nbsp; It means flopping around, invising around, porting out of the area etc don't really have anything to do with it, because in each of those cases you're avoiding battle, not engaging in it.&nbsp;&nbsp; The description doesn't say "Unmatched survivability to survive in general exploration", or "to survive while running away from an NPC", or anything else of the like.&nbsp; The clear implicit statement is that you are in battle while this "survival gene" is expressing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src="http://i12.photobucket.com/albums/a247/Ridefort/frodsig.gif" height=110 width=300><br><br>Warrior Class Correspondent<br>"54 random people is no more a raid than a heap of building materials is a house"
							</div>
								
