<HR>
Frodlin wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Sometimes BB gets portrayed as being inconsistent unfairly.&nbsp; I think this is one of those times. 
<HR>

<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>How?&nbsp; He's constantly stating that pulling singles is part of "surviving" less damage... he's constantly stating healing or lifetapping is part of "surviving" less damage.</P>
<P>Whenever I state that his unmatched survivability pertains to ONLY pure physical mitigation, which is the basis of Tanking... all we hear is the same Vindi tirades and whines about not having pulling techniques or rezzes.</P>
<P>This is a classic example of BB's double standard... Pulling is part of surviving and having better survivability... until it doesn't mesh with his current rant...</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I try to be fair as much as I can be.&nbsp; It's no real secret that BB and I disagree about the extent of this issue, but when I run the logic, I'm simply not seeing a contradiction here.&nbsp; I can say "BB, we disagree about the interpretation of the clause at hand", but I cannot say "double standard" or "contradiction".</P>
<P>Perhaps you can point me to where he states that pulling falls within the clause cited, all I've seen is other folks including it and going "see?&nbsp; FD is greater survival", then him responding to that allegation, then someone using said response to accuse him of invoking the argument in the first place.</P>
<P>I certainly don't think that pulling is "survival", it's crowd control, it's an ability.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I most certainly DO think that self healing is survival and that self healing and raw mitigation should be balanced with one another to acheive a level of parity, and that solo and pvp play MUST be factored as part of the overall balance equation, and that it's a darned shame that they've been ignored for so long.<BR></P>
