<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV><STRONG><EM></EM></STRONG><BR>There's no question that SoE/Verant is talking about the Warrior unmatched ability to survive <U>tanking</U>, not FDing, running away, porting, or standing out of AE range invis.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Thus, you survive tanking... which entails nothing more than mitigating incoming damage... better than every other class, with built in DI-1, better skillcaps, better returns from AC.&nbsp; Not splitting mobs to avoid damage from multiple mobs...</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<I><B><BR></B></I><BR>Warriors getting hit and mitigating better is meaningless. 
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>That's a classic.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR><BR>I'll try to help you over this cognitive hurdle. I am tanking - thanks to my avoidance and use of Evasive I survive. It's not unmatched mitigation that delivered that particular result, it was nonetheless tanking and surviving. There are any number of raid boss mobs where Warriors use Evassive rather than Defensive.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Evading damage from an engaged mob <EM><STRONG>is</STRONG></EM> mitigating over time the damage done to you.&nbsp; Sorry if that's a bit higher level than the other "cognitive hurdles" you tend to skip...&nbsp; Higher skillcaps in evasion skills... it's part of mitigating or reducing, or lessening the incoming damage.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR><BR>We're the masters of all weapons and tactics.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>And yet you can't use certain weapons... both class specific, archetype specific, theme specific, so many reasons why you can't use particular weapons.</P>
<P>Get over it... you can absolutely have what is fair... what you're asking for is not.<BR></P>
