		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV><I><B>If our DPS is really determined by our 2-hander set-ups, and you wish to argue that Warrior's shouldn't take a similair hit to use a shield, then really the knight costs are not appropriate either.</B></I><BR><BR>Nope, Knight DPS is a function of the importance of their spellbooks in their Total Class Power.<BR><BR>Let me put it this way. If in endgame content a Paladin does 400DPS and a Warriors does 700DPS, that's because your spellbook is extraordinarily powerful.<BR><BR>700DPS-400DPS = 300DPS (substitute 200DPS if that seems more reasonable to you). A rather arbitrary value for your spellbook, 300 DPS, but something to work with. Equip a shield. Can you do a 90% res, buff, Root, stun for an aggro event and another 6-8 seconds later? You can sir. Don't fib. 
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Yes, Knight DPS is very much a function of our Spellbooks, which is why I am a staunch opposer of those who have asked for DPS increases in the past, and I have posted very well reasoned replies to that effect on both Paladin and SK forums.</P>
<P>However, to use you illustration, you are very much correct, the gap of 700DPS to 400 DPS between a Warrior and a knight would be appropriate (these numbers not being entirely accurate of course) and Knights being on the low end of the DPS spectrum is also proper in conjunction with our spell power.</P>
<P>Knight 1-Hander DPS however being 40% of those prescribed numbers, in the 250 DPS range however is Broken, seriously and horribly&nbsp;broken. That Tunare that it has not yet reached that state (these being only illustrations mind you)</P>
<P>The current gap between Knight and Warrior DPS when a knight has a 2-Hander is low but tolorable and justified by our spellpower. This I suport full heartedly. However our DPS when we use a 1-Hander is something that has become more and more of a concern to me, in it's current state our 1-Hander DPS is rapidly approaching the state of being broken. It's borderline on this right now, however I personally do not think it is yet an issue as the upcoming expansion may change things in either direction.</P>
<P>I am not hiding anything as I firmly believe that Wariors should have appropriate weapons and aggro to use shields, I have always beleived and suported that. You need to face the fact that Knights do in fact pay a significant, though balanced and acceptable, price to use shields.</P>
<P>I've already demonstrated the increased cost in mana to hold aggro (which equates to a net loss in the number of other benificial spells I could have cast with that mana) this coupled with the heavy DPS loss is an appropriate cost to use a Shield. I think Warriors should pay a similair cost.</P>
<P><STRONG>"Warriors take a MUCH MUCH bigger hit in Total Class Power when using a shield"</STRONG></P>
<P>Yes, but we aren't suggesting you take the exact same percentage hit as a knight either. I suggest the cost should be between 20-30% depending on gear and advancement. This falls well within what Frodlin suggested earlier of 20%. The point is paying an appropriate cost while still maintaining supperior DPS to a knight in the same configuration.</P>
<P>"Total Class Power" would include your dramatically increased survivability while using a shield, there is imo no net loss to paying an appropriate cost.</P>
<P><STRONG>"You on the other hand not only get rediculously advantageous ratio weapons, still some pretty sweet Cleanses, etc."</STRONG></P>
<P>If they were rediculously advantageous ratios then they would be within 5% range of our 2-hander DPS, much as Warrior DWing DPS is so close to their 2-Hander DPS. </P>
<P>Cleanses are Paladin only and only effect undead. Furthermore we don't exactly do spectacular Undead damage with 1-hander weapons, so lets not confuse what I do with a 2-hander with what I do with a 1-hander.</P>
<P><STRONG>"I triple attack between 0 and 3 times in a reasonably long group mob fight. That's my dramatic DPS advantage with sword and board sir that's different than when we both weild 2Handers, not the BS that's been posted."</STRONG></P>
<P>Parse please. There are ample Warrior/knight 1-handers available in the game that it would be an easy task for you to Parse a Warrior vs a knight both using the same Sword and Board set-up. At least present a parse&nbsp;of&nbsp;a Warrior using a knight usable 1-Hander/shield</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
