Frodlin wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<P>Perhaps you can point me to where he states that pulling falls within the clause cited,
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
BattleBlade wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<DIV><I><B>Q1: How to you survive being hit by a mob?</B></I></DIV>
<DIV>A1: Being hit by a mob is VERY late in the survival game.<BR><BR>How do you avoid having more than one mob hit you? FD pull and only bring one mob to camp.</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>There are so many ways to out-survive pretty much every class.&nbsp; Shamans can out-survive a Warrior through heals and slows... Monks, Bards, Necros, SKs can all reduce a strain on a group by pulling less mobs.&nbsp; Clerics, Druids, Shaman, can all heal a group to survive.</P>
<P>Unmatched "survivability" and the best "tanking" needs to be quantitavely and qualitatively set before discussing what you are "entitled" to.</P>
<P>Or else you get the BB school of logic trying to teach you how surviving includes pulling and surviving doesn't include pulling.</P>
