		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Frodlin wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<P>I certainly don't think that pulling is "survival", it's crowd control, it's an ability.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I most certainly DO think that self healing is survival and that self healing and raw mitigation should be balanced with one another to acheive a level of parity, and that solo and pvp play MUST be factored as part of the overall balance equation, and that it's a darned shame that they've been ignored for so long.<BR></P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>It's hard to compare Solo and PvP to Grouping because there is a fundamental change in dynamics, they make poor group models. Take PvP, the simple tactic of jousting elliminates Weapon ratios so any comparision here of weapon damage does not carry over into groups. Another thing that comes into play is the concept of sustainable resources, obviously I cannot afford to expend my entire mana supply on each and ever mob I fight while grouped, nor could I cast the same numebr of spell son a mob that lives 30-45 seconds as opposed to one that lives for 5+ minutes.</P>
<P>Nor would I, by the same token, include Defensive in a comparison unless it was talking about a specific case where Defensive would be properly employed (like a raid event or particular mob) I consider Defensive something Warriors use in raids and as a zero factor in XP groups, just as I consider soloing Rhag or Vindi a zero factor in XP groups.</P>	
		</td></tr>
