			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Frodlin wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I certainly don't think that pulling is "survival", it's crowd control, it's an ability.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I most certainly DO think that self healing is survival and that self healing and raw mitigation should be balanced with one another to acheive a level of parity, and that solo and pvp play MUST be factored as part of the overall balance equation, and that it's a darned shame that they've been ignored for so long.<BR></P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Self-healing is survability to what ever extent it allows you to survive obviously. It's impossible to balance self healing and raw mitigation though, they have two completely different functions and one can never fully replace the other.&nbsp; I don't think solo ability should factor into group or raid balance as it has no relevance to grouping or raiding.&nbsp; At the end of the day when you are LFG no one cares if you could solo vindi or tormax they care how you are going to perform in the group. It's also pretty hard to balance soloing on it's own because abilities don't have solo only tags they can be used everywhere. Classes without significant self healing ability typically fare poorly in soloing unless they have a means of killing from a distance effectively.</P><p>Message Edited by Azazel420 on <span class=date_text>09-12-2006</span> <span class=time_text>02:57 PM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
