			<br><blockquote><hr>Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<br><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><i><b>and it is impossable to make warrior survie the best in all content if
your including things other then mitigation and avoidance.<br><br></b></i>Stuff and nonsence. HP recovery while tanking is obviously part of survival. Knights just wish it not to be.<br><br>Am I not getting standing regen? Do I not proc Life Saps? Do I not consume healing potions? It includes healing Grinder.<br>
<hr></blockquote>But it doesn't say healing who from, be it self, or
from others, it says nothing further at all, it doesn't mention what
such survival entails. If you're so obsessed about that one clause...
ask for them to expand upon it, because it is so vague.<br><blockquote><hr>Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<br><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><i><b>because at some point, a cleric will always survive where a warrior
cant simply because they can neutralize incoming DPS with their heals.<br><br></b></i>How is this possible Grinder? Is the "mitigation" of self-healers too great? Or is the self-healing of Warriors inadequate?<br><br>I'd prefer not to see the "mitigation" of self-healers reduced to where it <u>should</u>
be. I'd prefer that Wariror HP recovery was improved to something
reasonable - say enough to be able to solo Vindi - using the
capabilities that were around 2 whole years ago.<i><b><br>
</b></i><hr></blockquote>Cleric mitigation is thankfully where it
should be, thanks, it doesn't need reducing. The other 2 priests are
already worse off with a lower softcap and worse return.<br><blockquote><hr>
   
    
AC Mitigation Changes  Bards and Clerics<br>

  <br>

At the summit I spoke briefly with Boanerges about cleric AC mitigation
and the AC cap. The AC cap for clerics is higher than other priest
classes, and at the time <b>I also claimed that the return for AC over the
cap was better for clerics over other priest classes</b>. Looking over the
data, <b>I found this to be not true  currently clerics receive the same
returns from AC over the cap as other priests.</b><br>

  <br>

After evaluating this today, weve decided to go ahead and increase the
AC over the cap for clerics to match that of bards  so that bards and
clerics will have both the same AC cap and same returns from AC over
the cap, making their gains from AC be equal.<br>

  <br>

As far as bards are concerned, I also looked over the AC cap values for
their class. Currently, the AC value for bards is set to the same
values as that of monks and rogues. This seems to also be too low and
after evaluation, bards will have the same cap as clerics, which is a
higher value.<br>

  <br>

These two changes should give both clerics and bards more gains from AC from gear than before.<br>

  <br>

Message Edited by Zajeer-Dev on 10-05-2005 06:40 PM <br>

  <br>

-Zajeer<hr></blockquote>It is not because our mitigation is too great, it is because our self healing is <u>that potent</u>
to even allow poorer mitigation to suceed where lesser healing would
prevent it. To prove what I mean, I did it before, and after the AC
fix. That return adjustment + DoDH defensives resulted in 72 less dps
than when it was with b0rked AC, it was that bad, but I still did it.
To further prove what I mean... a druid only managed to do it in mostly
Deathknell gear, several months later, due to the lesser healing in
efficiency and power. It'll be a year tomorrow since he fell to broken
AC.<br>
<br>
You want enough to be able to solo vindi- in your gear? Say a warrior
is doing 450dps including that from damage shields, procs etc. Takes
about 8minutes 30seconds to kill him with that dps. Let's say hes doing
170 adps to a warrior, I'm pulling numbers out of the air here because
I forget what frodlin said the dps taken was on him. If damage was
constantly the same... in that time, you'd need to heal up 87550.
Surprisingly, similar to what Ning managed. Thus essentially, you wish
for a healing discipline that would do ~1020hp per tick the entire time
excluding potions, so factoring in potions (hot pots &gt; burst), it's
on average 702hp/tick for 5 ticks-30s, per 2 minutes. That makes the
healing from other sources required of 73510- 143 hps or 860 per tick
if just from a healing disc, lasting the entire 8 and a half minutes.
Is that reasonable? Any less, and you're dead because he will not die
before you will. Mull over it, because that is what it would require
+/- depending on RNG. Vindi has 200k with ~300hp/tick regen. I don't
see why he is such a point of fixation... he doesn't drop anything cool
(100hp bp is no longer the uberness it once was), and nameds in The
Hive who have far lesser hp (who can be slowed) drop much better if
you're after a cash cow.<br><div></div>
