			By expanding on that clause... the <u>how</u>, the crux of unmatched survivability. The "Like it or not" is not an explanation nor expansion on how.<br>
<br>
Knight mitigation is too good, despite being worse than a warriors?
They don't really use shields whilst soloing these mobs, the ones I see
just use 2.0/2.5s when doing so, even though Brael has recommended
haveing a shield up when doing so for certain npcs.<br>
<br>
I disagree that he is a good example of comparing "dpsing" tanks for
group content. No mobs in xp zones last 8minutes+, not one, apart the
irregulars like Msha's (who were never really meant to be grouped-
source prathun, not to mention they aren't really xp mobs anyways). <br>
<br>
You didn't comment on the healing that would be required. It is more
than your class would ever have, because you will never get something
on par with the GoD cleric elixir (which lasts 4ticks base, 7 with aa's
and buff extension) that would last the entireity of 85 ticks worth. If
you can see why that is, you'll know why it is unbalancing to want
that. So have hp healed in bursts? Fat good that will do, it needs to
be 'constant' and spread over the time it takes to kill him else again,
you'd die eventually.<br>
