		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><i><b>
   By expanding on that clause... the <u>how</u>, the crux of unmatched survivability.<br></b></i><br>No how is necessary. The result is sufficient. It's SoE job to figure out the how and thus far the original team was absolutely brilliant in coming up with a good "how" while the current team is "having issues". I'm enjoying outperforming the Warriors my now 69 Paladin competes with. I'd enjoy more actually playing my main, but that seems to be a bit beyond the current state of the art.<br><br>(Mind you making shields practical, potions, reigning in the totally unneeded WoT and DS spells, nerfing that pet pull exploit that 'splains why I couldn't buy a group for the last year all help.)<br><br>The "Like it or not" is a restatement of what the result is to be. Not confined to just raid mobs. We are <u>the masters</u> of armed defence and offence.<br><br><i><b>
Knight mitigation is too good, despite being worse than a warriors?<br><br></b></i>That certainly is a posibility that can't lightly be dismissed. If a Shaman could 99% equal your CH, had a much faster spell and and much bigger manapool, you'd be out of a job.<br><br>So it is with Wariors. If a Paladin has the same AC, similar returns on post softcap AC, etc. AND can heal up a storm beyond that then Warriors are out of a job.<br><br><i><b>
I disagree that he is a good example of comparing "dpsing" tanks for
group content.<br></b></i>It's perfectly fine to disagree and be wrong. He's little different from facing 16 group mobs one right after the other at a fairly liesurely pace (slow enough that a Warrior could actually Bazu each one of them).<br><br>Now clearly <u>part</u> of the problem was group content that was so trivial Warrior greater survivability was totally irrelavant. Crank up the difficulty of some portion of the content until Warirors begin as they should to survive better and it's a help. But that crank up has to include the FACT than in every group I've been in for over a year that was at ALL challanging Paladins are using WoT extensively. And before WoT existed, they cast heals.<br><br><i><b>If
you can see why that is, you'll know why it is unbalancing to want
that.<br></b></i><br>If it's unbalancing for a Warrior to want that, it is beyond obvious that it's unbalancing for Knights to actually HAVE it.<i><b><br></b></i><div></div><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>09-12-2006</span> <span class=time_text>06:22 PM</span>	
