<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=25790#M25790">1050</a> of 1172
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 163 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			The how is important actually. Because then it would outline how SoE
wants warriors to have unmatched survivability. Not how the players
want it, but how the devs envisage it. We clerics know how we are going
to be the best healers, because it is outlined we have unmatched power
and efficiency. That is not vague, it is saying, the best hpm heals,
and those with the best hps heals (which is true). "Unmatched
survivability", is vague and should be clarified.<br>
<br>
You see nothing wrong with 900 hp per tick, additive to elixirs and
other slot hp regens, that would effectively last 10 minutes? Knight's
dont have that- look at the recast on Pious Cleansing, the reuse timers
on the sk epic, paladin epic (since you're referring to 2 years ago
with Ning, he had no DS, he had no cast HoTs, potions iirc were not
available. It milked everything out of him, and was pretty close). If
you really want their sustainability calculated properly over the
course of 8-15 minutes, then it can easily be done so, but it is
nothing like a near constant Holy Elixir in disc form.<br>
<div></div>
